                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-16T11:00:00+00:20"
                            >April 16, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 16—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119. On Sunday Dutch anti-aircraft batteries and pursuit planes were in action
                    against British, French and German planes over Netherlands territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
